---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Newsletter from '../components/Newsletter.astro';
---

<Base
  title="About the Author | Richard L. Becker"
  description="Richard L. Becker is a Yale Law graduate, practicing family law attorney, and longtime youth hockey coach writing darkly comic fiction about corruption and justice in America."
>
  <section class="head">
    <div class="wrap split">
      <div class="portrait">
        <!-- Replace /public/author.jpg with Rich's approved portrait -->
        <img src="/author.jpg" alt="Richard L. Becker" />
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">About the Author</p>
        <h1>Richard L. Becker</h1>
        <p class="creds">
          Yale Law Graduate • Practicing Family Law Attorney • Longtime Youth Hockey Coach
        </p>

        <p>
          Imaginative, outrageous, and completely unconstrained, Richard L. Becker writes the
          fiction that most people are afraid to live. By day he practices family law — the front
          row seat to human nature at its rawest. By night and weekend he coaches youth hockey,
          where the stakes are supposedly lower and the behavior is somehow worse.
        </p>
        <p>
          He channels the corruption and absurdity he sees daily in the justice system and youth
          sports into compulsively readable novels that dare readers to keep turning the page. From
          a private investigator hired to seduce an assistant coach to characters who will do
          anything to win, his darkly comic stories explore a just person fighting an unjust world
          — where innocence defeats immorality or joins it.
        </p>
        <p>
          A concept grabs him, the music plays, and the characters take over. The result is raw,
          topical escapist fiction that delivers uncomfortable truths about love, greed, revenge,
          and redemption in America today.
        </p>

        <p class="dare">“Dare you to keep turning the page.”</p>

        <a class="btn" href="/books">Explore the Books</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Newsletter />
</Base>

<style>
  .head { padding-block: 5.5rem; }

  .split {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 2fr 3fr;
    gap: 3.5rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .portrait img {
    width: 100%;
    filter: grayscale(35%) contrast(1.05);
    border: 1px solid var(--hairline);
    position: sticky;
    top: 6rem;
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-top: 0.8rem;
  }

  .creds {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.76rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--bone-dim);
    margin: 0.8rem 0 1.8rem;
  }

  p + p { margin-top: 1rem; }

  .dare {
    margin: 1.8rem 0;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    color: var(--blood);
  }

  @media (max-width: 860px) {
    .split { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .portrait { max-width: 380px; }
    .portrait img { position: static; }
  }
</style>
